            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue Trinitatis. <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #childOf #heirTo" ref="#people/5020"
                            >Wilielmus</persName> divina favente clementia <rs key="#Marquis/duke"
                            >dux</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis #parentOf"
                            ref="#people/2498">Roggerii</persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">gloriosi</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ducis</rs>
                        <rs key="#heirTo">heres</rs> et <rs key="#childOf">filius</rs>. Convenit
                        omnes in regimine constitutos dominicis obedire preceptis atque ei per quem
                        regnat colla subicere, ut regni illius mereantur esse participes, quod fine
                        caret, quod semper sine iactura, sine merore durabit. Ob amorem igitur regis
                        celestis, per quem subsistimus, regimus atque regnamus, propter redemptionem
                        animarum predicti <rs key="#parentOf">genitoris</rs> nostri bone
                        recordationis necnon et <rs key="#grandparentOf">avi</rs> nostri <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Vir_magnificus #grandparentOf" ref="#people/2497"
                            >Robberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_magnificus">magnifici</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ducis</rs> et <rs key="#grandparentOf">avie</rs>
                        nostre <persName key="#grandparentOf" ref="#people/2496"
                            >Sikelgaite</persName> ducisse, pro salute quoque nostra nostreque <rs
                            key="#parentOf">genitricis</rs>
                        <persName key="#parentOf" ref="#people/5021">Hale</persName> omniumque <rs
                            key="#familyOf">parentum</rs> nostrorum, confirmamus et concedimus
                        monasterio <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/84">Beati
                            Benedicti sancti Casinensis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobii</rs> et tibi domno <persName
                            key="#Abbots #Personal_rank" ref="#people/4216">Girardo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Personal_rank">venerabili</rs>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs> eisdem monasterii tuisque successoribus in
                        perpetuum habenda et possidenda omnia que predictus genitor noster Roggerius
                        dux et avus noster Robbertus dux et avia nostra Sikelgaita ducissa in
                        prefato sancto cenobio Beati Benedicti Montis Casini obtulerunt; in primis
                        in Calabria <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Coloni/tenants #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3091">Sancte Anastasie</orgName> in <rs
                            key="#Village/castle_territory">territorio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Village/castle_territory" ref="#places/5130"><geogName
                                key="#Village/castle_territory" ref="#estates/3063"
                                >Follocastri</geogName></placeName> cum <rs key="#Coloni/tenants"
                            >hominibus</rs> et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> et omnibus
                        suis pertinentiis atque substantiis mobilibus et immobilibus, simulque et
                        totam <rs
                            key="#Fisheries #Fish #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >piscariam</rs> que specialiter tunnaria appellatur in <rs
                            key="#City_territory">territorio</rs> predicte <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitatis</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/5131"><geogName key="#City_territory"
                                ref="#estates/3064">Tropee</geogName></placeName>, loco qui
                            <placeName ref="#places/5132"
                            key="#Sea #Fisheries #Fish #Coloni/tenants">Bordella</placeName>
                        vocatur, cum <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">hominibus</rs> et omnibus suis
                        pertinentiis terra <rs key="#Sea">marique</rs> mobilibus et immobilibus; <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> quoque <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Coloni/tenants #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3092">Sancti Nycolai</orgName> in <rs
                            key="#Village/castle_territory">territorio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Village/castle_territory" ref="#places/5133"><geogName
                                key="#Village/castle_territory" ref="#estates/3065"
                                >Bisaniensi</geogName></placeName>, in <rs key="#Vici">vico</rs> qui
                            <placeName key="#Vici" ref="#places/5134">Sillictana</placeName>
                        dicitur, cum <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">hominibus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> et omnibus suis pertinentiis atque
                        substantiis mobilibus et immobilibus et cum omnibus rebus et hominibus que
                        in eodem loco domna <persName key="#childOf" ref="#people/5022"
                            >Rocca</persName> amita nostra <rs key="#childOf">filia</rs>
                        <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/5023">Drogonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> habuit et per <rs key="#Cartula">cartulam</rs>
                        Beato Benedicto obtulit; necnon et locum illum qui <placeName
                            ref="#places/2863"
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Forests #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Coloni/tenants #Ports #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Village/castle_territory #Monasteries"
                                ><geogName key="#Village/castle_territory" ref="#estates/3068"
                                >Cetrarius</geogName></placeName> dicitur, una cum toto <rs
                            key="#Ports">portu</rs> suo et cum omnibus suis pertinentiis atque
                        universis <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">colonis</rs> ibidem habitantibus et cum
                        omnibus etiam <rs key="#Monasteries">monasteriis</rs> intra pertinentias
                        predicti locis constitutis et cum omnibus ipsius <rs
                            key="#Village/castle_territory">territorii</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">pascuis, aquis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> ac pertinentiis omnibus mobilibus et
                        immobilibus terra <rs key="#Sea">marique</rs>; in <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities #Castle #City_territory" ref="#places/5135"
                                ><geogName key="#City_territory" ref="#estates/3066"
                                >Troia</geogName></placeName> vel in <rs key="#City_territory"
                            >territorio</rs> eius <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3093">Sancti Angeli </orgName>et <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3094">Sancti Thome</orgName> et <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3095">Sancti Bartholomei</orgName> que est
                        subtus <rs key="#Castle">castellum</rs> ipsius civitatis et <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3096">Sancte Iuste</orgName>, cum omnibus
                        pertinentiis atque substantiis earum mobilibus et immobillibus, <rs
                            key="#Castle">Castellonem</rs> quoque qui dicitur de <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Castle"
                            ref="#places/5136">Baroncello</placeName> in eodem territorio cum <rs
                            key="#Coloni/tenants">hominibus</rs> omnibusque suis pertinentiis
                        mobilibus et immobilibus; in territorio etiam eiusdem civitatis Troge <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Coloni/tenants #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3097">Sancti Nicandri</orgName> et <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Coloni/tenants #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3098">Sancti Nicolay que dicitur de
                            Gallitianis</orgName> cum <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">hominibus</rs> et
                        cum earum pertinentiis atque substantiis mobilibus et immobilibus; in <rs
                            key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/3432">Montis Sancti Angeli
                            </placeName><rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Hospitals"
                            >hospitale</rs> etiam cum <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            >ecclesiis</rs> et <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">hominibus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >terris</rs> et cum omnibus suis pertinentiis; in <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/84">Salerni</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/3702"
                            key="#Storage_units #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches #Monasteries"
                            >Sancti Laurentii</orgName> cum <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiis</rs> et
                        cum <rs key="#Storage_units">fundico</rs> ad portam <rs key="#Sea"
                            >maris</rs> et omnibus pertinentiis suis mobilibus et immobilibus; in
                            <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/2860">Malfitana</placeName>, in loco
                            <placeName key="#Storage_units" ref="#places/5137"
                        >Vallenole</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Storage_units #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >fundicum</rs> et <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3099">Sancti Benedicti</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3800">Sancti Blasii</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3703">Sancti Nicolai</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3801">Sancte Crucis.</orgName> Preterea
                        confirmamus vobis <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >terram</rs> quam olim in Traiano territorio, apud Sanctam Iustam,
                        concessimus in prephato monasterio Sancti Benedicti. Insuper concedimus
                        vobis ut <rs key="#Animals">animalia</rs> vestra, que annualiter in nostram
                        terram devenerint, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">pascua
                            in solitis locis habeant et absque nostra hominumque nostrorum vel
                            alicuius persone contrarietate vel infestatione seu reditione maneant et
                            redeant</rs>, excepto <rs key="#Public_exactions">quod Troia dare soliti
                            sunt</rs>. Hec itaque omnia que supra scripta sunt et cunctas alias
                        possessiones que per omnes terras nostri <rs key="#Marca/ducatum"
                            >ducatus</rs> sive principatus, patrociatus etiam aut <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatus</rs> prephato vestro monasterio quocumque
                        modo, id est divina vel humano iure pertinent, omnia libere et absolute
                        confirmamus et concedimus eidem monasterio Sancti Benedicti Montis Casini et
                        ti reverentissimo abbati domno Girardo, successoribus tuis imperppetuum, ea
                        ratione ut semper sint in potestate et dominatione predicti ei vestri
                        monasteri vestraque prenominate abbas, vestrorumque successores omnium ad
                        habendum et possidendum iure quieto imperppetuum, sine nostra nostrorumque
                        heredum aut successorum seu nostre rei publice exactorum omnisque humane
                        persone contrarietate vel molestatione. Si quis vero temerario ausu harum
                        nostrarum confirmationum vel concessionum aliquatenus violator extiterit,
                        sciat se iram Dei et nostri graviter incurrere et compositurum <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri purissimi libras mille</rs>, medietatem camere
                        nostre et medietatem prephato sancto monasterio seu rectoribus eius, absque
                        pagine huius aliqua infirmatione. Quod ut verius credatur et firmius omni
                        tempore observetur, <persName key="#Writer #Notary" ref="#people/5024"
                            >Iohanne</persName> nostro <rs key="#Notary">notario</rs> scribere
                        precepimus et nostro cum tipario aurea bulla insigniri iussimus anno
                        dominice incarnationis millesimo centesimo quartodecimo, ducatus autem
                        nostri anno quarto, mense Octobris, octava indictione. Ego Willielmus dux me
                        subscripsi. Ego <persName key="#Witness #Princeps" ref="#people/3019"
                            >Robbertus</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/173">Capuanorum</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs> me subscripsi. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/5025">Fulconis de Basumgerio</persName>. Ego
                            <persName key="#Witness #Other_palatine_officer" ref="#people/5026"
                            >Iohel</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">comestabuli</rs>. Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Professional_writer" ref="#people/5027"
                            >Landulfus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Professional_writer">protonotarius</rs> interfui et subscripsi.
                        Ego <persName key="#Witness #Count" ref="#people/5028">Willelmi
                            </persName><rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> de <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/5138"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3056"
                                >Principatu</geogName></placeName>. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
